notes: Match was delayed from 15th February due to rain and a flooded ground.
G Kirsten 50 off 51 balls, 100 off 105 balls, 150 off 135 balls

G Kirsten 188* off 159 balls, 4 sixes, 13 fours. Highest ever individual score in World Cup matches, surpassing IVA Richards' 181* v SL at Karachi in 1987. 2nd highest ODI score of all time, needing 3 off last ball to equal Viv Richards' all time ODI record score of 189.
South Africa's 321/2 is the 17th highest ever ODI total by any team, and the highest ever by South Africa.
Sultan Zarawani was struck on the head, without a helmet, by a Donald bouncer.
UAE 9th wicket partnership of 80* is the 2nd highest of all time (Arshad Laiq and S Dukanwala).

milestones.description: Gary Kirsten has scored 3 hundreds in ODIs, the most for SA breaking Hansie Cronje's record
Hansie Cronje has scored 15 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for SA breaking Andrew Hudson's record
Gary Kirsten's 188 is the highest individual score in ODIs (for SA), surpassing Callaghan's 169
Cullinan and Gary Kirsten's 145-run partnership is SA's highest for the 3rd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 118 between Hansie Cronje and Kallis
Arshad Laeeq and Dukanwala's 80-run partnership is UAE's highest for the 9th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 3 between Arshad Laeeq and Imtiaz Abbasi
Zarawani has conceded the most runs in an innings (69) in ODIs for UAE, going past Arshad Laeeq's record of 56
Hansie Cronje has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (78) for SA, going past Richardson
Arshad Laeeq has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (3) for UAE, going past Azhar Saeed
South Africa's 170-run win against U.A.E. is the largest margin of victory in terms of runs in ODIs, beating 157-run win against Pakistan
